Emerillon 0.1.90 (2011-09-07)
===============================

This release brings some major changes, like port to GSettings,
GTK+ 3.0, libchamplain 0.12 and libpeas.

New:
  #618851, Port to GSettings (Łukasz Jernaś)
  #626247, Migrate from PyGTK to PyGObject introspection-based bindings
  #628080, Use libchamplain 0.7.1 or newer for the map plugin
  #631879, Update librest to version 0.7
  #642786, Use libchamplain 0.10
  #649403, Support gtk3
  #656315, make distcheck fails (Laurent Bigonville)
  #658354, Please support libchamplain 0.12 (Laurent Bigonville)

Other changes:
  * Update DOAP info according to recent guidelines (Łukasz Jernaś)
  * Port main application to libpeas (Johannes Schmid)
  * search-plugin: Port to libpeas (Johannes Schmid)
  * placemarks-plugin: Port to libpeas (Andreas Henriksson)
  * copy-link-plugin: Port to libpeas (Andreas Henriksson)
  * map-position-plugin: Port to libpeas (Andreas Henriksson)
  * Use GtkBox instead of deprecated GtkVBox/GtkHBox (Andreas Henriksson)
  * Use cogl, clutter and gtk_clutter option groups (Laurent Bigonville)
  * Update version for instrospection files (Łukasz Jernaś)
  * Remove dropped manager section from reference docs Łukasz Jernaś)

Added/updated translations:
  * ar, courtesy of Khaled Hosny
  * ca, courtesy of Gil Forcada
  * el, courtesy of Evangelos Vafeiadis
  * he, courtesy of Yaron Shahrabani
  * hu, courtesy of Gabor Kelemen
  * it, courtesy of Claudio Arseni
  * lv, courtesy of Rudolfs Mazurs
  * nb, courtesy of Kjartan Maraas
  * ro, courtesy of Lucian Adrian Grijincu
  * ru, courtesy of Yuri Myasoedov
  * sv, courtesy of Daniel Nylander
  * uk, courtesy of Daniel Korostil
  * vi, courtesy of Lê Trường An
  * zh_CN, courtesy of YunQiang Su

Emerillon 0.1.2 (2010-06-25)
===============================

This release includes some minor fixes and completion
of the GSEAL GNOME goal.
Also experimental GObject introspection has been added
Thanks go out to Simon Wenner and the translators.

New:
  #616729, Vala bindings (Simon Wenner)
  #616389, support specifying lat/lon on the command line
  #620601, Initial user documentation (Mario Blättermann)

Bug fixes:
  #614575, fix build with GTK+ 2.20  (Andreas Henriksson)
  #615725, use accessor functions
  #606757, command line argument handling

Other changes:
  * Use Automake silent rules (Simon Wenner)
  * Sidebar: Fix display bugs (Simon Wenner)
  * Save and restore the window size (Simon Wenner)
  * Buildsystem: Improve the configure output (Simon Wenner)
  * Placemark plugin: replace deprecated function
  * Placemark plugin: display markers on the map
  * Added gtk-doc based documentation
  * Added GObject introspection support
  * Ported to libchamplain 0.6.x

New and updated translations:
  * cz, courtesy of Marek Černocký
  * da, courtesy of Joe Hansen
  * de, courtesy of Mario Blättermann
  * es, courtesy of Jorge González
  * fr, courtesy of Bruno Brouard
  * gl, courtesy of Fran Diéguez
  * it, courtesy of Claudio Arseni
  * jp, courtesy of Takeshi AIHANA
  * nb, courtesy of Kjartan Maraas
  * pl, courtesy of Aviary.pl
  * pt, courtesy of António Lima
  * pt_BR, courtesy of Michel Recondo and Hugo Vaz Sampaio
  * sl, courtesy of Matej Urbančič
  * zh_CN, courtesy of Sun Ning

Emerillon 0.1.1 (2010-01-09)
===============================

Small update to include small bug fixes and translation updates.

Fixes:
* COPYING is GPLv2
* Enable scale is built against libchamplain 0.4.3
* Fix some memory leaks
* Sidebar: turn on ellipsizing
* Map Position: remove from status bar on disable
* Search: select the row when the marker is selected
* Search: remove layer on disable
* Reset zoom actions after changing the map-source
* Fix .desktop file (Debarshi Ray)
* Add Fullscreen mode (Simon Wenner)
* Fix translations (Łukasz Jernaś)

Added/updated translations:
 * ar, courtesy of Khaled Hosny
 * da, courtesy of Joe Hansen
 * de, courtesy of Mario Blättermann
 * es, courtesy of Jorge González
 * id, courtesy of Andika Triwidada
 * is, courtesy of Anna Jonna Armannsdottir
 * ja, courtesy of Takeshi AIHANA
 * lv, courtesy of "Last-Translator:
 * pt_BR, courtesy of Vladimir Melo
 * sl, courtesy of Matej Urbančič
 * sv, courtesy of Daniel Nylander

